OL,3,CEngland prepare to face DR Congo in
OL,4,Cfirst World Cup knockout game
OL,6,FAmongst those likely to start for the
OL,7,FAfrican side are Aaron Wan-Bissaka of
OL,8,FWest Ham and Burnley's Axel Tuanzebe,
OL,9,Fboth of whom suffered relegation to
OL,10,Fthe Championship with their teams in
OL,11,FMay.
OL,13,FYoane Wissa of Newcastle ` who is the
OL,14,Fteam's top scorer at the tournament `
OL,15,FSunderland's Noah Sadiki and Watford's
OL,16,FEdo Kayembe have also helped the side
OL,17,Fto some eye-catching results in the
OL,18,Fgroup stage.
